15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Reciprocity in gender transition treatment coverage required. (1) A
16 group or individual insurance policy that includes coverage for gender transition treatment or subsequent
17 treatment directly related to the provision of gender transition treatment must also include coverage for
18 detransition treatment under equivalent cost-sharing policies.
19 (2) If the group or individual insurance policy ceases coverage for gender transition treatment, the
20 policy is not required to provide equivalent coverage for detransition treatment, except that the policy must
21 provide equivalent coverage to insureds who were enrolled when gender transition treatment coverage was
22 provided and received benefits under that coverage.
